<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8469&amp;p=88089#p88089"><![CDATA[
I am thinking of trying to mod an american NES to add microphone support and before I start messing around with the idea I wanted to try to find a test rom that could check if the mic is registering as it should to test the final mod. Yeah, it is a pretty stupid plan I know but I wanted to celebrate the recent translation of Takeshi no Chōsenjō by actually playing it:0 I wanted to waste my time with that game ever since the Gamecenter CX episode where Arino finish the game:) Plus I wonder how the translation team dealt with the karaoke portion of the game... I suppose they translated the lyrics in english to something that sound the same to the low-fi mic of the famicom... I'm curious about this.<br /><br />I found the schematic of the mic input on the board (<a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=7094&amp;start=0&amp;postdays=0&amp;postorder=asc&amp;highlight=microphone" class="postlink">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=7094&amp;start=0&amp;postdays=0&amp;postorder=asc&amp;highlight=microphone</a> but not sure if it has ever been done before. Well, I can't figure out why someone would have done that just to be able to scream at pols in Zelda but I've seen weirder thing happen before <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br /><br />Anyway, any input or idea on how to add the mic to a NES would be also appreciated!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4859">SkinnyV</a> — Wed Dec 28, 2011 8:05 pm</p><hr />
